critique: This document is an executive order that withdraws land from settlement, location, sale, or entry, and reserves it for public use. It cites the Act of Congress approved June 25, 1910, as amended, and section 10 of the act of December 29, 1916. There is no direct indication of ideological tilt, immigration approach, executive power expansion, federalism implications, national security vs. civil liberties concerns, economic regulation, or social inclusion considerations. The action appears to be a routine land management decision.
